Avena sterilis

   [3572.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3572

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION An erect grass and grain crop, 50-120 cm tall. USES
   The grain is made into porridge and oatmeal or fed to livestock.
   GROWING PERIOD Annual. COMMON NAMES Sterile oat, Animated oat. FURTHER
   INF Sterile oat is primarily a weedy spieces. It's latitudinal range is
   between 55°N-34°S, and it can be found at elevations up to 2000 m.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 43 [USE]
   Duke J 1979 pp 94 [RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Duke J 1975 pp 8 [RAIN, TEMP, PH]
   Baum B 1977 pp 334-350 [DEP, FER, DRA, TEXT, LIMITS]
   Ibrahim K 1987 pp 84 [LIMITS]

